Miscellaneous Highlights: The Houston Astros claimed their sixth division title in seven seasons.
The Astros will have an automatic berth in the ALDS.
The Texas Rangers needed a victory or a Houston Astros loss to secure the AL West, but the Seattle Mariners played spoiler, taking down the Rangers 1-0.
The Marlins were able to hold on to the fifth seed despite a loss in the final game.
The Wild Card Round may commence with Minnesota hosting Toronto and Tampa Bay hosting Texas in the AL, while Milwaukee will host Arizona and Philadelphia will host Miami in the NL.
Others: The MLB postseason bracket is officially set.
All participants had secured a spot by Saturday night, but Sunday's action had quite the impact on seeding.
The seeding for the American League is: 1. Baltimore Orioles, 2. Houston Astros, 3. Minnesota Twins, 4. Tampa Bay Rays, 5. Texas Rangers, 6. Toronto Blue Jays.
The seeding for the National League is: 1. Atlanta Braves, 2. Los Angeles Dodgers, 3. Milwaukee Brewers, 4. Philadelphia Phillies, 5. Miami Marlins, 6. Arizona Diamondbacks.
